      "title": "Cyrano De Bergerac 1900 Directed By Clement Maurice",
      "description": "Cyrano de Bergerac (1900) Director: Clément Maurice Cyrano de Bergerac is a 1900 French short drama film directed by Clément Maurice, featuring Benoit Constant Coquelin as Cyrano. It was shown at the 1900 Paris Universal Exposition. The film, tinted with color and synchronized to a wax cylinder recording, is thought to be the first film made with both color and sound.",
